 in urban space is examined through its different components — design, city and technology actants. This unveils the unpredictable nature and emerging potential of performance art as it unfolds in the machinic city, which consists of assemblages of efficient and not-so-efficient machines.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArt and technology. 0aArt, Municipal. 0aCities and townsxEffect of technological innovations on. 0aCity and town lifexPsychological aspects. 0aMachinery in art. 0aPerformance artvCase studies. 0aPerformance artxSocial aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aBlast Theory.  aFélix Guattari.  aart.  aavant-garde.  adigital.  ainteractive.  amachine.  aparticipation.  aperformance art.  aurban.1 aDias, Marcos P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packagez978311128198840uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152613579740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526135797423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526135797/original  a978-3-11-128198-8  Manchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packageb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles